Description: Body sherd of Milesian Fikellura pottery amphora; white slip; exterior: part of painted lotus bud and lotus flower frieze with added purple on lozenge in between two narrow brown bands (only traces remaining); below, part of lozenge from one lotus flower.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GF.080)
